Run from dockerfile + docker-compose
====================================

 => Dockerfile + docker-compose.yml files


    docker-compose build
or
    docker-compose build --no-cache django

then

    docker-compose up


initialize django with
    docker-compose exec django python manage.py migrate
    docker-compose exec django python manage.py createsuperuser
    ...

access the app with
    firefox localhost:8080














========================================================================


0) create project

  oc new-project dummy_django


1) build

  first time only (create build)
  oc new-build --name=dummy_django --strategy=docker --code=https://github.com/phyver/dummy_django

  then
  oc start-build dummy_django

1-bis) read logs

  oc logs -f bc/dummy_django


2) deploy

  first time only
  oc apply -f deployment.yaml

3) expose service and route

  first time only
  oc expose deployment dummy_django --port=8080
  oc expose svc/dummy_django

